<h2 style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">10 Box Strip</h2>

<div style="line-height:2">
<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">The 10 Box Strip contains 10 boxes. Use this visual tool to explore the number pairs of 10 with counters. Drag the red counter to fill up the boxes from left to right. When the red counter filled the boxes desired, click the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_visibility.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">For example, when a red counter is dragged in the first box, the remaining nine empty boxes will be filled with the yellow counters when you click the button. The mathematical sentence will automatically appear according to the red and yellow counters.</p>
</div>